If the pound rose, by 3% against the US dollar ($) between December and the following January, what would $200 then be worth in GB pounds (£)? (2 decimal places)
In December, we have that £1 is worth \$1.48. If the pound rose by 3% by the following January, we get that in January:

\begin{align*}£1 &= \$1.48 \times 1.03\\
&= \$1.5244.\end{align*}
So after this 3% rise, £1 is worth \$1.5244.
Multiplying both sides of this equation by 200 and then dividing by 1.5244, we get:

\begin{align*}\$200 &= £1 \times \frac{200}{1.5244}\\
&= £131.1991...\end{align*}
So, to two decimal places, \$200 is now worth £131.20.
